A detachnment of Nigeria Police in Abuja has taken over the Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) to prevent anarch over plans by some elements to take over the football house as a means of enforcing the judgement of the Supreme Court on the leadership crisis rocking Nigerian football. The heavily armed detachment numbering over 25 came it two trucks and a car and stood guard inside and outside the premises. One of the officers, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said they were there to ensure that miscreants do not enter the premises to forment trouble. The mobilization of the police was not unconnected to snippet of information that Ambassador Chris Giwa was planning to storm the office to take over the the affairs of the federation. 0 comments